The '''White House Conference on Small Business''' was a series of three conferences that occurred in 1980, 1986, and 1995.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wharton|first=Jody|title=THE WHITE HOUSE CONFERENCES ON SMALL BUSINESS, 1980-1995|url=http://www.sbaer.uca.edu/research/sba/1995/pdf/16.pdf|accessdate=22 April 2013|year=2004}}</ref> They were convened by [[President of the United States|presidents]] [[Jimmy Carter]], [[Ronald Reagan]] and [[Bill Clinton]] in an effort to foster better relationships with members of the business community and to develop innovative policy solutions to economic problems.<ref>{{cite news|last=Richman|first=Tim|title=The White House Small Business Conference|url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/19861101/4070.html|accessdate=22 April 2013|newspaper=Inc. Magazine|date=Nov 1, 1986}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Reagan|first=Ronald|title=Executive Order 12523 -- National White House Conference on Small Business|url=http://www.reagan.utexas.edu/archives/speeches/1985/62785e.htm|publisher=White House|accessdate=22 April 2013|date=June 27, 1985}}</ref><ref name="Business1990">{{cite book|author=United States. Congress. House. Committee on Small Business|title=National White House Conference on Small Business: hearing before the Committee on Small Business, House of Representatives, One Hundred First Congress, second session, on H.R. 4773 ... Washington DC, May 22, 1990|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1wP6HoEmVP0C|accessdate=22 April 2013|year=1990|publisher=U.S. G.P.O.}}</ref>
